cs.DC, cs.DB, cs.DS, cs.PL, cs.SE 

Reasoning: 
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) is the most likely category as the paper is about a distributed batch data processing framework. 
- cs.DB (Databases) is also likely as the paper discusses data structures and operations commonly used in databases. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is relevant as the paper discusses the use of arrays as a primary data structure and the use of template meta-programming to optimize performance. 
- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is relevant as the paper discusses the programming interface of the Thrill framework. 
- cs.SE (Software Engineering) is relevant as the paper discusses the design and performance evaluation of a software framework.
